         <abstract>
            <p>The article discusses the background of the new plan for supplementing present sources of international liquidity, some of the surrounding economic and political issues, the features of the plan and how it will operate once it has been activated. The conclusion is that the new mechanism, though clearly a compromise, is highly flexible and has great potential for future growth and evolution. It augurs well for continued international financial stability and expansion of world trade, and definitely should minimize the possibility of any major international financial crisis. N.B. Please see addendum on page 13.</p>
